# Blog Posts Directory

Place your blog posts in this directory. Each post should be a Markdown file with front matter.

## File Naming Convention

Blog posts should follow this naming pattern:
- `YYYY-MM-DD-post-title.md` (e.g., `2026-04-08-my-first-post.md`)
- `YYYY-MM-DD-post-title/index.md` (for posts with images/assets)

## Front Matter Template

```markdown
---
slug: post-url-slug
title: Your Post Title
authors: [author_key]
tags: [tag1, tag2, tag3]
---

Your post summary (shown in list view).

<!--truncate-->

Full post content goes here...
```

## Front Matter Options

- **slug**: URL-friendly identifier (optional, defaults to filename)
- **title**: Post title
- **authors**: Array of author keys from authors.yml
- **tags**: Array of tags for categorization
- **date**: Override date (optional, defaults to filename date)
- **image**: Cover image URL
- **hide_table_of_contents**: true/false
- **draft**: true to hide from production builds

## Assets

For posts with images or other assets, create a folder:
```
blog/
  2026-04-08-my-post/
    index.md
    image1.png
    image2.png
```

Then reference images: `![Alt text](./image1.png)`
